<p>Apologies. I'd meant to remove a line permitting generic Tales lists. What role would this list serve/what category should this go in?</p>
<p>It <em>seems</em> like you're suggesting a general list of &quot;Must reads&quot; or &quot;Notable&quot; tales&#8230;now, I am trying to get something like that up - in the hub, it's stated that we need:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Top Tales for &quot;Ambassador&quot; category<br />
Goal is two (2) lists of 10. One list for series, one list for stand-alones.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>While here you've got mostly one-shots, with a tale series grouped in as well; not to mention that this is a list of eight, and the first rule requests lists of 10:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Proposals should contain at least 10 articles.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I've gone ahead and changed 'should' to 'must', and clarified that rule some. The vague wording is my fault.</p>
<p>Beyond that, I could get behind a couple of these - although it's mostly rehashing the Top Rated Tales, so it doesn't strike me as something the majority of the readership isn't already going to come across, so the proposal feels insubstantial. Now that I've cleared some things up (again, apologies), you're welcome to give this some more structure.</p>
<p>And The Dr Bright List doesn't belong on here.</p>

