			<div class="content" id="post-content-3819736">
									

<p>I've just accepted a different proposal for Ambassador series, given that this is pretty much just a list of Canons.</p>
<p>For the stand-alones:</p>
<p>I wouldn't include anything here that is part of an active contest, either (so no SoaG). I'll make another update to note this.</p>
<p>bwbwbwbwbwg and DRFTMT are two good choices (despite their prominence on Top Rated of All Time - I've seen them as recommendations countless times). The Clef-Kondraki Tale is a decent way to get into all the old AA shenanigans, but it's really heavy on the links and references, so it might work better for 'series' (though it <em>technically</em> isn't one). Similarly,<br />
Habil &amp; Quabil and Containment Breach the Musical are both super-referential as well.</p>
<p>Magic Orientation <em>is</em> part of a collaborative series (MTF contest).</p>
<p>Until Death isn't a bad choice - I feel that it can be enjoyed as a horror Tale without needing prior context of the two SCPs.</p>
<p>One of the Anomalous Items Tales wouldn't be a terrible idea, but none of them have ever been outstanding and aren't anything I'd recommend a new reader.</p>
<hr />
<p>So, for this, I'll accept bwbwbwbwbwg, Document Recovered From The Mariana's Trench, and Until Death. I'd like to slide &quot;<a href="/his-name">His Name</a>&quot; in there as well, because it's a pretty damn stellar self-contained work.</p>

